Larger U.S. Companies Gave CEOs Higher Bonuses in 2010, WSJ Says

-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 
2011-03-18T01:02:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/larger-u-s-companies-gave-ceos-higher-bonuses-in-2010-wsj-says.html
Chief executive officers at 50 U.S.
corporations with at least $4 billion in revenue, including Walt
Disney Co. and  Starbucks Corp. (SBUX) , received an average of 30.5
percent more in bonus compensation last year than in 2009, the
Wall Street Journal reported, citing analysis done by consulting
company Hay Group.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  